Change your mind change the chemistry! Stress and anxiety are the causes of 90% of diseases and weight gain! Guess what?....It all started in our head and yes we can change it! 💪🧠 #stressmanagement 

6 WAYS TO MANAGE YOUR STRESS & ANXIETY:

✅  Create a routine - Patterns and routines help our minds feel more organized and less overwhelmed. Focused on healthy habits; For example, establishing a solid nighttime routine (like turning the tv off by 10pm, brushing your teeth, and being in bed with a book by 10:30). 

✅ Practice deep breathing - It’s crazy how much something as instinctive as breathing can affect our everyday stress levels. When feeling stressed or anxious, practice this breathing exercise: breathe deeply for 4 counts, hold for 3 seconds, and release slowly for 6 counts. Repeat 3-5 times.

✅ Make a to do list - Organize your day / week and prioritize your schedule depending on your goals. Know the difference between: Urgent, important, can wait. This will help you to be more productive less overwhelmed and more focused and in control. 

✅ Reduce time watching news and social media - Focused on self growth, reading a book, listening to products… 

✅ Exercise and meditation - Move your body, be active outdoor or at the gym; cardio, yoga and weight training can helps you relax and recharge your body and mind with positive energy.

✅ Sleep - 7-9 hours sleeping will help you recover and reduce your stress hormones (cortisol).

At the age 29 I changed my all life! I quit my job, change my career, stopped smoking, eat healthy, lost weight, started to run and lifting weights in the gym for the first time in my life! In the beginning I couldn’t run 2min, but I never gave up until I was able to run 10K and It felt amazing!!! After participating in several races I decided to focus on building muscle mass to be able to compete. 

At the age 35 I competed first time in my life in bodybuilding! All this time that I changed myself everyone said that I’m crazy, but I never listen to them only to my heart! I felt in love in this sport and from there I never stop. I continued to compete and became a professional bodybuilding, that was my BIG DREAM and I’m very happy that I was able to achieve it! I also very proud to be the first and the only Israeli female IFBB PRO. 🏆🇮🇱🇺🇸

All this didn’t happen by mistake it all starts with a DECISION to change my life and do what makes me happy! Take control on your body and your life. Always evolve to be the best of yourself! 💪😁
